column1: Created by Eric Barefoot, modified by George Allen
This table is field data collected in a subcatchment of the Stony Creek Watershed in Duke Forest Edeburn Division SW of Hillsborough, North Carolina
This data set was created by Eric Barefoot and Elizabeth Henry by flagging streams every 5 meters and then measuring wetted width of flowing streams with a tape measure
This data was collected to determine the distribution of stream widths in headwater catchments.

column2: Internal and external stream segments usually seperated by nodes. Order is arbitrary

Estimated percentage of the streams that were not flowing due to sandbars, rocks, vegetation, or other material at the surface of the stream
